Perfect! Now I have all the information I need. Let me create a comprehensive summary report.

## Summary Report: Repost Card Rendering Implementation

Based on my analysis of the iskrib_v3 codebase, here's how repost cards render embedded original post content:

### Key Files and Components:

#### 1. **PostCards.jsx** - Main Feed Component
**File:** `/client/src/components/HomePage/postCards/PostCards.jsx`

This is the primary component that handles rendering both normal posts and reposts in the feed. Key implementation details:

**Lines 533-546:** Repost detection and content parsing:
```javascript
const isRepost = journal?.is_repost === true;
const isCanvasPost = !isRepost && journal?.post_type === 'canvas';
const parsedContent = !isRepost ? ParseContent(journal.content) : null;
// ... 
// For repost cards: parse original post content for preview
const repostSource = isRepost ? journal?.repost_source : null;
const repostSourceParsed = repostSource ? ParseContent(repostSource.content) : null;
const repostSourcePreviewText = repostSourceParsed?.slicedText || '';
```

**Lines 563-617:** Repost Card Structure:
```javascript
{isRepost && (
    <div className="repost-header-badge">
        {/* Repost indicator badge */}
        <span onClick={(e) => handleClickUserProfile(...)} className="repost-header-name">
            {journal.users.name}
        </span>
        <span>reposted</span>
    </div>
)}

{isRepost ? (
    <div className="card-content">
        {journal.repost_caption && (
            <p className="repost-caption-text">{journal.repost_caption}</p>
        )}
        {repostSource ? (
            <div className="repost-embedded-card" onClick={(e) => {
                e.stopPropagation();
                // Navigate to original post
                viewContent(
                    e,
                    repostSource.content,
                    sourceParsed?.wholeText || '',
                    repostSource.title,
                    repostSource.users?.id,
                    repostSource.users?.name,
                    repostSource.users?.image_url,
                    repostSource.created_at,
                    repostSource.id,
                    false, 0, false, 0, 0,
                    repostSource.users?.badge,
                    repostSource.post_type,
                    repostSource.canvas_doc
                );
            }}>
                <div className="repost-embedded-author">
                    <img className="repost-embedded-avatar" src={repostSource.users?.image_url} />
                    <span className="repost-embedded-name">{repostSource.users?.name}</span>
                    <VerifiedBadge badge={repostSource.users?.badge} size={12} />
                </div>
                <p className="repost-embedded-title">{repostSource.title}</p>
                {repostSourcePreviewText && (
                    <p className="repost-embedded-text">{repostSourcePreviewText}</p>
                )}
            </div>
        ) : (
            <div className="repost-unavailable">
                This post is no longer available
            </div>
        )}
    </div>
)}
```

**Lines 706-718:** Repost Button Logic:
```javascript
{icon.repostAction && journal.users.id !== userId && (
    <div onClick={(e) => {
        e.preventDefault();
        e.stopPropagation();
        if(!session) return openAuthModal();
        // If this post is a repost, use the original post for reposting
        const journalForModal = journal.is_repost && journal.repost_source
            ? { id: journal.repost_source.id, title: journal.repost_source.title, users: journal.repost_source.users }
            : journal;
        setRepostModalJournal(journalForModal);
    }} id="card-icons" className={icon.className}>
        {icon.repostIcon}
    </div>
)}
```

#### 2. **RepostModal.jsx** - Repost Creation Component
**File:** `/client/src/components/RepostModal/RepostModal.jsx`

Handles the modal for creating a repost with optional caption:

**Lines 64-75:** Original post preview in modal:
```javascript
<div className="repost-original-preview">
    <div className="repost-original-author">
        <img className="repost-original-avatar"
             src={journal?.users?.image_url || '/assets/profile.jpg'} />
        <span className="repost-original-name">{journal?.users?.name}</span>
        <VerifiedBadge badge={journal?.users?.badge} size={12} />
    </div>
    <p className="repost-original-title">
        {journal?.title?.length > 80 ? journal.title.substring(0, 80) + '...' : journal?.title}
    </p>
</div>
```

#### 3. **ContentView.jsx** - Single Post Viewer
**File:** `/client/src/components/HomePage/ContentViewer/ContentView.jsx`

Displays individual posts with repost functionality:

**Lines 516-541:** Repost modal integration:
```javascript
{showRepostModal && postData && (
    <RepostModal
        journal={{
            id: postData.journalId,
            title: postData.title,
            users: {
                id: postData.userId,
                name: postData.name,
                image_url: postData.avatar,
                badge: postData.badge
            }
        }}
        onClose={(result) => {
            setShowRepostModal(false);
            if(result === 'success'){
                setBookmarkedMessage('Post was reposted');
                // Toast notification
            }
        }}
    />
)}
