**The app is completely open**: Unauthenticated users can:
1. Navigate to any route (no client-side guards)
2. View all public journal posts with full content
3. See author info, like counts, comment counts
4. Read all comments on posts

**They CANNOT**:
1. Like, bookmark, or comment (auth modal blocks these actions)
2. Access private journals (server checks `privacy === 'public'`)
3. View their own profile or bookmarks

This is intentional design - posts are public by default unless marked private.

